-- DirecTV to Pay $13 Million to Settle Consumer Claims
-- B y   K a r e n   F r e i f e l d
-- 2010-12-15T17:26:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/directv-to-pay-13-million-to-settle-49-state-consumer-protection-claims.html
DirectTV, the largest U.S.
satellite-television provider, will pay $13.25 million plus
restitution to settle allegations by 49 states over alleged
consumer protection violations.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Freifeld in New York at 
 kfreifeld@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
